 and more established ones which are now being affected due to various opportunities and pressures in contemporary societies.  The book is split into two parts, the first (Chapters one to four) reviews key theoretical and conceptual debates in this field, while the second (Chapter five to nine) offers insights and an understanding of exchange practices based on case studies from different regions and different relationships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAgingvCross-cultural studies. 0aIntergenerational relationsvCross-cultural studies. 0aOlder peoplevCross-cultural studiesxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aColeman, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelmajer, Pascale F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGanong, Lawrence H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIzuhara, Misa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIzuhara, Misa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJoseph, Ricky, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLowenstein, Ariela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOduaran, Akpovire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOduaran, Choja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847422064423C